<div style="background-color:#fdfdfd;font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;">As you may have heard, Horizon Workspace 1.8 became GA yesterday.Â This release hasn't been publicized too much but is a major improvement over the 1.5 release with many bug fixes. Some of the major changes include:</div>
<div style="background-color:#fdfdfd;"></div>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>Citrix-based Application integration.</b>Â From the Horizon Workspace User Portal, users can launch Citrix-based applications via XenApp 5.0, 6.0, and 6.5 using single sign-on. Note: Citrix Receiver must be installed on the client.</li></ul>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>VMware ThinApp package delivery to Windows desktops.</b>Â Horizon Workspace provides delivery of ThinApp 5.0 packages with 32-bit/64-bit applications to all Windows devices. HTTP delivery is supported to non-domain member endpoints on Windows devices.</li></ul>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>Microsoft Office 365.</b>Â Single sign-on from Workspace to Microsoft Office 365, SharePoint, and Outlook 365 web applications. Browser based and native email clients are supported.</li></ul>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>Horizon Workspace User Portal and App Center.</b>Â The User Portal has been enhanced to make application resource management easier. The App Center provides users with self-service category filtering, which shows the latest applications added.</li></ul>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>Web application links.</b>Â IT administrators can now create Web application links that do not require user authentication, allowing administrators to create static Web links.</li></ul>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>Enterprise enhancements, including the following.</b></li></ul>
<ul style="font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;"><li><b>Support for multi-forest Active Directory deployments.</b>Â You can integrate Horizon Workspace with multiple Active Directory (AD) forests.</li></ul>
<ul style="font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;"><li><b>Application access policy.</b>Â IT administrators can apply access policies and select different authentication methods based on application type.</li></ul>
<ul style="font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>Support for enterprise branding of Horizon Workspace.</b></li></ul>
<ul style="background-color:white;font-family:verdana, tahoma, helvetica;font-size:13px;"><li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><b>VMware Switch enhancements, including the following.</b></li></ul>
<ul style="font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;"><li><b>Support for Android 4.2 (JellyBean) as the workspace operating system.</b></li></ul>
<ul style="font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;"><li><b>Support for Android tablets.</b></li></ul>
<ul style="font-family:'times new roman', 'new york', times, serif;font-size:16px;"><li><b>Enhanced Horizon Mail 1.7x.</b></li></ul>
